Hello All,

We are working on the migration windows phone 8.1 project to UWP project under VS2015 update 3.
We are facing some unknown issue when we enable .net native tool chain for C# application.

Our C# project is calling WRT component written in C++/CX, in C++/CX, there is a function as below :
```
bool NameSpace::test(IVector<IVector<int>^>^ rtVector) {
	Vector<int>^  each = ref new Vector<int>();
	each->Append(1);
	each->Append(2);
	each->Append(3);

	rtVector->Append(each);  --> Exception throw if enable .net native tool chain
	return true;

}

```
In C# project, to call this function: 
 ```
  List<IList<int>> d = new List<IList<int>>();
  bool  b = obj.test(d);
```
I steped in append function, the exception was thrown by below: 
`
System.Runtime.InteropServices.SharedCcw_IVector.Append(System.IntPtr, System.IntPtr)`


The exception ONLY happened when we enable .net tool chain in C# project.
If we disable this option, it works fine.

Thanks for your help.
Best Regards,
Yingjie

